  "text": "Mean concentrations of tHcy in the present study were similar [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] or lower than others in young women [CITATION_3] or in a random population sample [CITATION_4] . Small doses of folate have been shown to reduce tHcy in a young population [CITATION_5] so the high blood folate levels observed in the present study may be protective of hyperhomocysteinaemia, which was found in 2% of women in this study, half of that in previous reports in young women [CITATION_6] .",
